div.bibl: Svenska Kuriren, Oct. 28, 1926GIVES FIFTY-FIRST ANNUAL CONCERT

body.p: Its 51st Annual Concert will be given by The Chicago "Swedish Wasa Society" in the evening of Nov. 13th in St. Matthews Swedish Evangelical Lutheran Church, corner of 80th and Aberdeen Streets. Among other attractions, the program offers singing by the Chicago "Swedish Glee Club", conducted by William Nordin.
"Wasa" is next to the oldest Swedish sick benefit and aid society in Chicago.
